    <annotation>
        
        <marginalia hand="English_secretary">
            <language ident="EN">
                <position place="left_margin" book_orientation="0">
                    <marginalia_text>The finding of the Gold Mine 1579. and 1576 after the stronger star in Cassiope appering.</marginalia_text> 
                </position>
            </language>
        </marginalia>
        
        <marginalia hand="English_secretary">
            <language ident="EN">
                <position place="right_margin" book_orientation="0">
                    <marginalia_text>I did coniecture the blasing star in Cassiopea appering a&o_super; 1572, to signifye the fynding of som[m]e great threasor or the philosophers stone: 
                        and what to end it did therein signifye, that it should concerne me somwhat. This I told to M[iste]r Ed Dier.
                        at the same tyme. How truely it fell out a&o_super; 1582. Martij 10 it may appere in tyme to come</marginalia_text> 
                    <symbol_in_text name="Trine"/>
                    <person name="Edward Dyer"/>
                </position>
            </language>
            <language ident="LA">
                <position place="right_margin" book_orientation="0">
                    <marginalia_text>ad stuporem Mundi</marginalia_text>
                </position>
            </language>
            <translation>I did conjecture the blazing star in Cassiopeia appearing in the year 1572, to signify the finding of some great treasure or the philosophers stone: and in fact it did [..] This I told to Mr Ed Dier at the same time. How truly it fell out 
            in the year 1582. March 10 it may appear in time to come to the marvel of the world.</translation>
        </marginalia>
        
        <marginalia hand="Italian">
            <language ident="LA">
                <position place="right_margin" book_orientation="0">
                    <marginalia_text>ei</marginalia_text> <!--JG: Unsure about this marginalia, doesn't seem to be an errata-->
                </position>
            </language>
            <translation>For him.</translation>
        </marginalia>
        
